<tr>
	<td width="1%">&nbsp;</td>
	<td width="98%">
  
		<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
		<tr>
		    <td valign="top">
		     <p><font face="Verdana" size="3"><b>Article Title:</b>&nbsp;</font>
		     <font face="Verdana" size="2">Evening Gordon bits from the official boards</font><br>
		     <a href = "../Subscribe.asp?DID=211143" ><font face="Verdana" size="2">[Subscribe to this document]</font></a></p>
			 </td>
		</tr>
		
		<tr><td>&nbsp;</tr><tr>
		
		    <td valign="top"><div style= "padding:4;float: right"> <script language=JavaScript src=http://www.obsidian-tech.com/absolutebm/abmx.aspx?z=26></script></div><p><font face="Verdana" size="2">
		    <Blockquote>
<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/010003.html">Three questions for the A-meister</a></B><P>

1) Can you tell me if Verant has any near-future plans to add a new zone or two to the established world via an optional two hour patch :P that would let us explore the new zone? Kudos on Paineel and recently The Hole. <P>

<B>We do have additional free zones planned, with the Warrens being the next one on the list. I'll have to check on Tuesday to see how this is coming along. I think that it will still be a few weeks before we'll see this go live.</B><P>

2) If you do implement a new zone, could you please just announce "A new zone is available via the optional patch, and that no new information is to be released about this area. Explore!<P>

<B>I like the sound of that, of course it would only be a secret until it ended up on the Test server :)</B><P>

There are no new zones for the lower levels. Can you bring this up at the next tuning meeting?? (Please?)<P>

<B>The issue here is that there is already a vast number of areas for the lower level folks out there. They are not the ones who are running out of content. Furthermore, since they are low level, they progress rather quickly from one set of zones to another, meaning that enjoyment of any new specifically low-level zone would be fleeting. It's the mid and upper levels that are typically most in need of new content.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/010068.html">Unannounced change in mountain giants? Abashi please repsond</a></B><P>

Well I have been camping mountain giants for a few weeks now, solo with my jboots, im a 34 wizard and it seemed at first they had a very LOW resistance to Bonds of Force and Root, well since the last patch they are resisting those spells almost every other cast and I am getting trampled, I would just like to know if I was getting extremely unlucky or it was an unnanounced change, thank you.<P>

<B>To be honest, I really don't know if the changes mentioned above occurred, but it's not really something that'd I'd go check on either. We don't announce standard tweaks to NPCs, as that is part of gameplay that is subject to change at any time. I will tell you that NPC resistances versus a particular line of spells cannot be set separately, so if they are more resistant it's probably because their magic resistance was increased.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/010202.html">CS question for you Gordon if you could please answer</a></B><P>

I know it is within your power to create and return the items I have lost (some of which no longer exist in the game), and I realize the dilemma I put you in. However, that being said, and given you statements above, don't I deserve the benefit of the doubt especially when it might cost you my account (don't want to take the time to re-equip my level 53 warrior) and maybe even my future business? <P>

<B>I understand your prediciment, however we are limited to the duration of our logs, and what we know to be true. In this case, any time you give your login information to someone else, you are essentially giving them permission to take your stuff. It's roughly the same as if you had handed the items off yourself. Though we don't have the logs going back six months to see when the items were taken, the information you've given is enough to see that we couldn't do a reimbursement for the sake of the integrity of the gaming environment. We can't allow the duplication of items to be as simple as giving out your account info out then contacting a GM for replacement.<P>

Had we the logs for when your stuff disappeared, we could certainly track down the recipient of your belongings and take action against them. We could then give you back anything that we recovered from the offending party. In this case, we know that the items still exist, and can't just duplicate them given the information you've provided.
<P>
I'm sorry that we couldn't help you in this matter.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/010205.html">PENDING GOD CHANGES AND THE REPRECUSSIONS.</a></B><P>

Anybody who did not buy Kunark would be losing
a feature they always had, the ability to go on
raids on the planes and face down the Gods.<P>

<B>Not really, there is nothing to say that they can't participate in one form or another. But even if we assume that what you are saying is basically true, they are losing the ability to kill an NPC named "XXX". That's basically it.<P>

Here's the situation. The deities and dragons are meant to be top level encounters. We made an exception with Vox and Nagafen and kept them where they were even though the level cap went up. In order to do this, we had to place the level restriction on those encounters.<P> 

The same situation is present with the deities, and the solution that we have is a compromise. Vox and Nagafen remained the same yet higher level folks can't attack them, and the deities will increase in power, so the lower level folks won't be able to attack them. At the same time we are taking the loot from the current deities and moving it to NPCs that are equivalent in power to the current deities.<P> 

Leaving things as they are now is not a reasonable option. This is the best option available to us.<P> 

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/010248.html">New Server?</a></B><P>

Well things change all the time. Anyway I thought they were still having an increase in subscribers so that should mean a new server. I haven't seen any official response on the question of a new servers. <P>

<B>Subcription numbers are indeed increasing, but we still have several servers that are below their optimal usage level at peak. Secondly, a larger portion of our increasing numbers are coming from overseas due to our arrangment with Ubisoft. These players aren't typically reflected in peak usage.<P> 

When we have concrete information on new/new-split servers, we'll be sure to let everyone know.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/010249.html">Impressed with Verant and EQ</a></B><P>

I'm still having a hard time grasping this concept... so is Verant REALLY always adjusting the balance of EQ and adding content such as new items and new quests and new storyline? Does Verant REALLY listen to suggestions and implement changes based off of the intelligent and popular suggestions? Does Verant plan to do this until the end of Everquest's lifespan? This is scary, I'm afraid I might have to stay addicted to this newfound game forever. I only just recently started with EQ, and browsing everlore.com, and it seems that all of the above is true...<P>

<B>I certainly like to think so :) We continue to want your business and can't expect to get that without some effort on our part.</B><P>

Verant is doing much to remove the static parts of the game (loot, spawns). My advice is to not stay in one spot, move around. Go somewhere you have never been. When that feeling of danger leaves your stomach, move to another spot. Explore this world that they have created; it is truly amazing. As with anything, it could be better, but nothing compares.<P>

<B>Good advice, and thanks for the testemonial :)</B><P>

For the most part, with the exception of Rogues for picking locks, the first three classes are the best in the game; the others really aren't too important except for "variety." <P>

<B>"Best" is highly subjective. The "best" class should be the class you find most exciting to play. I, for instance, would not play a cleric because I'm not in to their style of play. However for someone who likes being depended on in game, the cleric is very well-suited. <P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/010263.html">Abashi, You might have been given bad info by the live team on this issue...</a></B><P>

Roror is still level 49, and still KOS to people. He is not on the Beta Neutral Faction. A level 49 SoW speed MoB that is KOS to everyone, in a newbie zone. If this was supposed to be fixed, it didn't go live.<P>

<B>Erm, that was supposed to be patched. I'll let them know. Thanks.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/010264.html">tracking how to imrpove? plz read abashi</a></B><P>

I have had an idea to be able to change your tracking range if you want to change how far you want to track (short range, med range and far range) once you first hit a level skill in tracking like 150 or something you should be able to change this. <P>

When in OT I try to avoid dragoons by tracking but sometimes they don't pick up and they are right beside me sometimes =(. I think that the 3 lvls of tracking ranges would change this.<P>

<B>We indeed have some ideas for tracking based upon the ideas presented here on the boards. Some of the ideas we are thinking about (and as a caveat, these are not guaranteed as future enhancements): /con colors listed in the tracking window, scrollbar, additional filters. Most if not all enhancements that will be implemented going forward will be restricted to the ranger class.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/010282.html">Why don't you adopt better boards?</a></B><P>

There's two problems that seem to continually plague these boards that are easily resolved:<P>

<B>We are in the process of writing a new board script completely in-house. If you have solutions in mind, please post them.</B><P>

These aren't the only message boards I frequent on the web, and these problems are not insurmountable.<P>

<B>I daresay that this is probably one of the most active messageboards on the net. I think that you'd have to go to the usenet to find a busier forum.</B><P>

1) People constantly post new replies to old posts to get Gordon to see them. Now, not only that, there are now threads about how best to get Gordon to respond to a topic.<P>

<B>It's going to happen whatever we adopt. This is a discussion forum, rather than a queued help list. I of course can't respond to every discussion, nor would that be what we are trying to accomplish.<P>

-Gordon</b><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/010290.html">Tolan's Darkwood Gauntlets ( WHY?)</a></B><P>

I cant think of anything positive on them.<P>

<B>How's the AC? Items aren't supposed to all be completely useful from every standpoint. The Kunark armor that people have been finding typically has high AC and little in the way of stats, aside from a piece or two. You have to decide if the AC and the spell attached to each piece is worth giving up another piece of armor from a different place.<P>

I would say that someone mixing and matching pieces of the high level armors is probably better off overall than the person who wears a complete set of one kind or another.<P>

-Gordon</B>
</blockquote>
		    </font></p>
			 </td>
		</tr>
